<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-11-14T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-11-14T00:00:00-05:00" n="657" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d657">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">693.003/574</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Chinese Chargé</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Tung Kwai</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-11-14"><hi rend="italic">November 14,
                                        1919</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                            <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to inform you that I
                                have received a cablegram from the Waichiao Pu (Ministry of Foreign
                                Affairs), dated <pb facs="0769" n="667" xml:id="pg_667"/> the 8th
                                instant, authorizing me to sign with you a treaty between China and
                                the United States giving effect to the new Chinese Import Tariff as
                                revised by the Tariff Commission which completed its labors at
                                Shanghai on December 20, 1918.</p>
                            <p>Accept [etc.]</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Yung Kwai</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>